body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Hughes Motors customer service. My name is Edward Hughes. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Carolyn. How are you feeling today?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: That's great to hear! Can you please provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's two four five six.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. I also need to verify your mailing address. Can you spell out the number of your house for me, Carolyn?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's seven two eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Carolyn. I appreciate your cooperation. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that will be all. Thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for contacting us, Carolyn. Have a wonderful day!
